{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28cdd2867ffe0IuY0ZM162vj27","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d7322e94c001apK8dLXx37JHcK","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7322f2ce0012XKGi0LxCKasGe","messageID":"msg_d7322e94c001apK8dLXx37JHcK","sessionID":"ses_28cdd2867ffe0IuY0ZM162vj27","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_39fe582eb7c0461e993a2a6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: <h1 align=\"center\">\n2:     <img alt=\"cookiecutter Logo\" width=\"200px\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter/main/logo/cookiecutter_medium.png\">\n3: </h1>\n4: \n5: <div align=\"center\">\n6: \n7: [![pypi](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cookiecutter.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cookiecutter/)\n8: [![python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cookiecutter.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cookiecutter/)\n9: [![PyPI Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/personalized-badge/cookiecutter?period=total&units=INTERNATIONAL_SYSTEM&left_color=BLACK&right_color=GREEN&left_text=downloads)](https://pepy.tech/projects/cookiecutter)\n10: [![GitHub Stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/cookiecutter/cookiecutter?style=flat&logo=github&label=stars)](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter)\n11: [![discord](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-cookiecutter-5865F2?style=flat&logo=discord&logoColor=white)](https://discord.gg/9BrxzPKuEW)\n12: [![docs](https://readthedocs.org/projects/cookiecutter/badge/?version=latest)](https://readthedocs.org/projects/cookiecutter/?badge=latest)\n13: \n14: </div>\n15: \n16: # Cookiecutter\n17: \n18: Create projects swiftly from **cookiecutters** (project templates) with this command-line utility. Ideal for generating Python package projects and more.\n19: \n20: - [Documentation](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io)\n21: - [GitHub](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter)\n22: - [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/cookiecutter/)\n23: - [License (BSD)](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter/blob/main/LICENSE)\n24: \n25: ## Installation\n26: \n27: Install Cookiecutter as a CLI tool with [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/):\n28: ```\n29: uv tool install cookiecutter\n30: ```\n31: \n32: ## Features\n33: \n34: - **Cross-Platform:** Supports Windows, Mac, and Linux.\n35: - **User-Friendly:** No Python knowledge required.\n36: - **Versatile:** Compatible with Python 3.10 to 3.14.\n37: - **Multi-Language Support:** Use templates in any language or markup format.\n38: \n39: ### For Users\n40: \n41: #### Quickstart\n42: \n43: The most common way to use Cookiecutter is as a command line utility with a GitHub-hosted Cookiecutter template such as https://github.com/audreyfeldroy/cookiecutter-pypackage\n44: \n45: **Use a GitHub-hosted Cookiecutter template**\n46: \n47: ```bash\n48: # You'll be prompted to enter values.\n49: # Then it'll create your Python package in the current working directory,\n50: # based on those values.\n51: # For the sake of brevity, repos on GitHub can just use the 'gh' prefix\n52: $ uvx cookiecutter gh:audreyfeldroy/cookiecutter-pypackage\n53: ```\n54: \n55: **Use a local template**\n56: \n57: ```bash\n58: $ uvx cookiecutter cookiecutter-pypackage/\n59: ```\n60: \n61: **Use it from Python**\n62: \n63: If you plan to use Cookiecutter programmatically, please run `uv add cookiecutter` to add it to your project. Then you can import and use it like this:\n64: \n65: ```py\n66: from cookiecutter.main import cookiecutter\n67: \n68: # Create project from the cookiecutter-pypackage/ template\n69: cookiecutter('cookiecutter-pypackage/')\n70: \n71: # Create project from the cookiecutter-pypackage.git repo template\n72: cookiecutter('gh:audreyfeldroy/cookiecutter-pypackage')\n73: ```\n74: \n75: > If Cookiecutter saves you time, [star it on GitHub](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter) so other developers can find it too.\n76: \n77: #### Detailed Usage\n78: \n79: - Generate projects from local or remote templates.\n80: - Customize projects with `cookiecutter.json` prompts.\n81: - Utilize pre-prompt, pre- and post-generate hooks.\n82: \n83: [Learn More](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage.html)\n84: \n85: ### For Template Creators\n86: \n87: - **Any language, any framework.** A Cookiecutter template is just a directory with variables. It works for Python, Rust, Terraform, docs sites, whatever you build repeatedly.\n88: - **Hooks for the rest of the setup.** Pre- and post-generate scripts (shell or Python) handle git init, dependency installs, or anything else your boilerplate needs.\n89: - **One file defines the interface.** `cookiecutter.json` declares every variable and its default. Users answer prompts; the template does the rest.\n90: \n91: [Learn More](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/)\n92: \n93: ## Available Templates\n94: \n95: Discover a variety of ready-to-use templates on [GitHub](https://github.com/search?q=cookiecutter&type=Repositories).\n96: \n97: ### Special Templates\n98: \n99: - [cookiecutter-pypackage](https://github.com/audreyfeldroy/cookiecutter-pypackage)\n100: - [cookiecutter-django](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter-django)\n101: - [cookiecutter-pytest-plugin](https://github.com/pytest-dev/cookiecutter-pytest-plugin)\n102: - [cookiecutter-plone-starter](https://github.com/collective/cookiecutter-plone-starter)\n103: \n104: ## Community\n105: \n106: Join the community, contribute, or seek assistance.\n107: \n108: - [Troubleshooting Guide](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/latest/troubleshooting.html)\n109: - [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/cookiecutter)\n110: - [Discord](https://discord.gg/9BrxzPKuEW)\n111: - [File an Issue](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter/issues?q=is%3Aopen)\n112: - [Contributors](AUTHORS.md)\n113: - [Contribution Guide](CONTRIBUTING.md)\n114: \n115: ### Feedback\n116: \n117: We value your feedback. Share your criticisms or complaints constructively to help us improve.\n118: \n119: - [File an Issue](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter/issues?q=is%3Aopen)\n120: \n121: ### Waiting for a Response?\n122: \n123: - Be patient and consider reaching out to the community for assistance.\n124: - For enterprise support, contact support@feldroy.com.\n125: \n126: ## Code of Conduct\n127: \n128: Adhere to the [PyPA Code of Conduct](https://www.pypa.io/en/latest/code-of-conduct/) during all interactions in the project's ecosystem.\n129: \n130: ## Acknowledgements\n131: \n132: Created and led by [Audrey M. Roy Greenfeld](https://github.com/audreyfeldroy), supported by a dedicated team of maintainers and contributors.\n\n(End of file - total 132 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<h1 align=\"center\">\n    <img alt=\"cookiecutter Logo\" width=\"200px\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter/main/logo/cookiecutter_medium.png\">\n</h1>\n\n<div align=\"center\">\n\n[![pypi](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cookiecutter.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cookiecutter/)\n[![python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cookiecutter.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cookiecutter/)\n[![PyPI Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/personalized-badge/cookiecutter?period=total&units=INTERNATIONAL_SYSTEM&left_color=BLACK&right_color=GREEN&left_text=downloads)](https://pepy.tech/projects/cookiecutter)\n[![GitHub Stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/cookiecutter/cookiecutter?style=flat&logo=github&label=stars)](https://github.com/cookiecutter/cookiecutter)\n[![discord](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-cookiecutter-5865F2?style=flat&logo=discord&logoColor=white)](https://discord.gg/9BrxzPKuEW)\n[![docs](https://readthedocs.org/projects/cookiecutter/badge/?version=latest)](https://readthedocs.org/projects/cookiecutter/?badge=latest)\n\n</div>\n\n# Cookiecutter\n\nCreate projects swiftly from **cookiecutters** (project templates) with this command-line utility. Ideal for generating Python package projects and more.\n\n- [Documentation](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775753163904,"end":1775753163916}}}]}
